55 template <>
56 const char* flowSymbol<START_IF_MASK>(InterfaceFlags f) {
57  f = f & START_IF_MASK;
58  if (f == READS_START)
59  return "→";
60  if (f == WRITES_PREV_END)
61  return "←";
62  if (f == UNKNOWN)
63  return "?";
64  return "↔";
65 }
66 
67 template <>
68 const char* flowSymbol<END_IF_MASK>(InterfaceFlags f) {
69  f = f & END_IF_MASK;
70  if (f == READS_END)
71  return "←";
72  if (f == WRITES_NEXT_START)
73  return "→";
74  if (f == UNKNOWN)
75  return "?";
76  return "↔";
77 }

102 InterfaceFlags StagePrivate::interfaceFlags() const {
103  InterfaceFlags f;
104  if (starts())
105  f |= READS_START;
106  if (ends())
107  f |= READS_END;
108  if (prevEnds())
109  f |= WRITES_PREV_END;
110  if (nextStarts())
111  f |= WRITES_NEXT_START;
112  return f;
113 }

115 void StagePrivate::validateConnectivity() const {
116  // check that the required interface is provided
117  InterfaceFlags required = requiredInterface();
118  InterfaceFlags actual = interfaceFlags();
119  if ((required & actual) != required) {
120  boost::format desc("actual interface %1% %2% does not match required interface %3% %4%");
121  desc % flowSymbol<START_IF_MASK>(actual) % flowSymbol<END_IF_MASK>(actual);
122  desc % flowSymbol<START_IF_MASK>(required) % flowSymbol<END_IF_MASK>(required);
123  throw InitStageException(*me(), desc.str());
124  }
125 }

127 bool StagePrivate::storeSolution(const SolutionBasePtr& solution) {
128  solution->setCreator(this);
129  if (introspection_)
130  introspection_->registerSolution(*solution);
131 
132  if (solution->isFailure()) {
133  ++num_failures_;
134  if (!storeFailures())
135  return false; // drop solution
136  failures_.push_back(solution);
137  } else {
138  solutions_.insert(solution);
139  }
140  return true;
141 }

143 void StagePrivate::sendForward(const InterfaceState& from, InterfaceState&& to, const SolutionBasePtr& solution) {
144  assert(nextStarts());
145  if (!storeSolution(solution))
146  return; // solution dropped
147  me()->forwardProperties(from, to);
148 
149  auto to_it = states_.insert(states_.end(), std::move(to));
150 
151  solution->setStartState(from);
152  solution->setEndState(*to_it);
153 
154  if (!solution->isFailure())
155  nextStarts()->add(*to_it);
156 
157  newSolution(solution);
158 }
159 
160 void StagePrivate::sendBackward(InterfaceState&& from, const InterfaceState& to, const SolutionBasePtr& solution) {
161  assert(prevEnds());
162  if (!storeSolution(solution))
163  return; // solution dropped
164  me()->forwardProperties(to, from);
165 
166  auto from_it = states_.insert(states_.end(), std::move(from));
167 
168  solution->setStartState(*from_it);
169  solution->setEndState(to);
170 
171  if (!solution->isFailure())
172  prevEnds()->add(*from_it);
173 
174  newSolution(solution);
175 }

177 void StagePrivate::spawn(InterfaceState&& state, const SolutionBasePtr& solution) {
178  assert(prevEnds() && nextStarts());
179  if (!storeSolution(solution))
180  return; // solution dropped
181 
182  auto from = states_.insert(states_.end(), InterfaceState(state)); // copy
183  auto to = states_.insert(states_.end(), std::move(state));
184 
185  solution->setStartState(*from);
186  solution->setEndState(*to);
187 
188  if (!solution->isFailure()) {
189  prevEnds()->add(*from);
190  nextStarts()->add(*to);
191  }
192 
193  newSolution(solution);
194 }

196 void StagePrivate::connect(const InterfaceState& from, const InterfaceState& to, const SolutionBasePtr& solution) {
197  if (!storeSolution(solution))
198  return; // solution dropped
199 
200  solution->setStartState(from);
201  solution->setEndState(to);
202 
203  newSolution(solution);
204 }

206 void StagePrivate::newSolution(const SolutionBasePtr& solution) {
207  // call solution callbacks for both, valid solutions and failures
208  for (const auto& cb : solution_cbs_)
209  cb(*solution);
210 
211  if (parent() && !solution->isFailure())
212  parent()->onNewSolution(*solution);
213 }

237 void Stage::reset() {
238  auto impl = pimpl();
239  // clear solutions + associated states
240  impl->solutions_.clear();
241  impl->failures_.clear();
242  impl->num_failures_ = 0u;
243  impl->states_.clear();
244  // clear pull interfaces
245  if (impl->starts_)
246  impl->starts_->clear();
247  if (impl->ends_)
248  impl->ends_->clear();
249  // reset push interfaces
250  impl->prev_ends_.reset();
251  impl->next_starts_.reset();
252  // reset inherited properties
253  impl->properties_.reset();
254 }

256 void Stage::init(const moveit::core::RobotModelConstPtr& robot_model) {
257  // init properties once from parent
258  auto impl = pimpl();
259  impl->properties_.reset();
260  if (impl->parent()) {
261  try {
262  ROS_DEBUG_STREAM_NAMED("Properties", "init '" << name() << "'");
263  impl->properties_.performInitFrom(PARENT, impl->parent()->properties());
264  } catch (const Property::error& e) {
265  std::ostringstream oss;
266  oss << e.what();
267  // skip this stage and start error reporting at parent
268  impl->parent()->pimpl()->composePropertyErrorMsg(e.name(), oss);
269  throw InitStageException(*this, oss.str());
270  }
271  }
272 }

286 void Stage::forwardProperties(const InterfaceState& source, InterfaceState& dest) {
287  const PropertyMap& src = source.properties();

337 void StagePrivate::composePropertyErrorMsg(const std::string& property_name, std::ostream& os) {
338  if (property_name.empty())
339  return;
340  os << "\nin stage '" << name() << "': ";
341  try {
342  const auto& p = properties_.property(property_name);
343  if (p.defined()) {
344  os << "defined here";
345  return;
346  } else
347  os << "declared, but undefined";
348 
349  if (p.initsFrom(Stage::PARENT))
350  os << ", inherits from parent";
351  if (p.initsFrom(Stage::INTERFACE))
352  os << ", initializes from interface";
353  } catch (const Property::undeclared&) {
354  os << "undeclared";
355  }
356  if (parent()->parent())
357  parent()->pimpl()->composePropertyErrorMsg(property_name, os);
358 }

367 std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const StagePrivate& impl) {
368  // starts
369  for (const InterfaceConstPtr& i : { impl.prevEnds(), impl.starts() }) {
370  os << std::setw(3);
371  if (i)
372  os << i->size();
373  else
374  os << "-";
375  }
376  // trajectories
377  os << " " << flowSymbol<START_IF_MASK>(impl.interfaceFlags() | impl.requiredInterface()) << " ";
378  os << std::setw(3) << impl.solutions_.size();
379  os << " " << flowSymbol<END_IF_MASK>(impl.interfaceFlags() | impl.requiredInterface()) << " ";
380  // ends
381  for (const InterfaceConstPtr& i : { impl.ends(), impl.nextStarts() }) {
382  os << std::setw(3);
383  if (i)
384  os << i->size();
385  else
386  os << "-";
387  }
388  // name
389  os << " / " << impl.name();
390  return os;
391 }

401 // initialize pull interfaces to match requested propagation directions
402 void PropagatingEitherWayPrivate::initInterface(PropagatingEitherWay::Direction dir) {
403  switch (dir) {
404  case PropagatingEitherWay::FORWARD:
405  required_interface_ = PROPAGATE_FORWARDS;
406  if (!starts_) // keep existing interface if possible
407  starts_.reset(
408  new Interface([this](Interface::iterator it, bool /*updated*/) { this->dropFailedStarts(it); }));
409  ends_.reset();
410  return;
411  case PropagatingEitherWay::BACKWARD:
412  required_interface_ = PROPAGATE_BACKWARDS;
413  starts_.reset();
414  if (!ends_) // keep existing interface if possible
415  ends_.reset(new Interface([this](Interface::iterator it, bool /*updated*/) { this->dropFailedEnds(it); }));
416  return;
417  case PropagatingEitherWay::AUTO:
418  required_interface_ = UNKNOWN;
419  return;
420  }
421 }
422 
423 void PropagatingEitherWayPrivate::resolveInterface(InterfaceFlags expected) {
424  if (expected == UNKNOWN)
425  throw InitStageException(*me(), "cannot initialize to unknown interface");
426 
427  auto dir = PropagatingEitherWay::AUTO;
428  if ((expected & START_IF_MASK) == READS_START || (expected & END_IF_MASK) == WRITES_NEXT_START)
429  dir = PropagatingEitherWay::FORWARD;
430  else if ((expected & START_IF_MASK) == WRITES_PREV_END || (expected & END_IF_MASK) == READS_END)
431  dir = PropagatingEitherWay::BACKWARD;
432  else {
433  boost::format desc("propagator cannot satisfy expected interface %1% %2%");
434  desc % flowSymbol<START_IF_MASK>(expected) % flowSymbol<END_IF_MASK>(expected);
435  throw InitStageException(*me(), desc.str());
436  }
437  if (configured_dir_ != PropagatingEitherWay::AUTO && dir != configured_dir_) {
438  boost::format desc("configured interface (%1% %2%) does not match expected one (%3% %4%)");
439  desc % flowSymbol<START_IF_MASK>(required_interface_) % flowSymbol<END_IF_MASK>(required_interface_);
440  desc % flowSymbol<START_IF_MASK>(expected) % flowSymbol<END_IF_MASK>(expected);
441  throw InitStageException(*me(), desc.str());
442  }
443  initInterface(dir);
444 }

481 void PropagatingEitherWayPrivate::compute() {
482  PropagatingEitherWay* me = static_cast<PropagatingEitherWay*>(me_);
483 
484  if (hasStartState()) {
485  const InterfaceState& state = fetchStartState();
486  // enforce property initialization from INTERFACE
487  properties_.performInitFrom(Stage::INTERFACE, state.properties());
488  me->computeForward(state);
489  }
490  if (hasEndState()) {
491  const InterfaceState& state = fetchEndState();
492  // enforce property initialization from INTERFACE
493  properties_.performInitFrom(Stage::INTERFACE, state.properties());
494  me->computeBackward(state);
495  }
496 }

576 void MonitoringGenerator::setMonitoredStage(Stage* monitored) {
577  auto impl = pimpl();
578  if (impl->monitored_ == monitored)
579  return;
580 
581  if (impl->monitored_ && impl->registered_) {
582  impl->monitored_->removeSolutionCallback(impl->cb_);
583  impl->registered_ = false;
584  }
585 
586  impl->monitored_ = monitored;
587 }

589 void MonitoringGenerator::init(const moveit::core::RobotModelConstPtr& robot_model) {
590  Generator::init(robot_model);
591 
592  auto impl = pimpl();
593  if (!impl->monitored_)
594  throw InitStageException(*this, "no monitored stage defined");
595  if (!impl->registered_) { // register only once
596  impl->cb_ = impl->monitored_->addSolutionCallback(
597  std::bind(&MonitoringGeneratorPrivate::solutionCB, impl, std::placeholders::_1));
598  impl->registered_ = true;
599  }
600 }

630 template <Interface::Direction other>
631 void ConnectingPrivate::newState(Interface::iterator it, bool updated) {
632  // TODO: only consider interface states with priority depth > threshold
633  if (!std::isfinite(it->priority().cost())) {
634  // remove pending pairs, if cost updated to infinity
635  if (updated)
636  pending.remove_if([it](const StatePair& p) { return p.first == it; });
637  return;
638  }
639  if (updated) {
640  // many pairs might be affected: sort
641  pending.sort();
642  } else { // new state: insert all pairs with other interface
643  InterfacePtr other_interface = pullInterface(other);
644  for (Interface::iterator oit = other_interface->begin(), oend = other_interface->end(); oit != oend; ++oit) {
645  if (!std::isfinite(oit->priority().cost()))
646  break;
647  if (static_cast<Connecting*>(me_)->compatible(*it, *oit))
648  pending.insert(make_pair<other>(it, oit));
649  }
650  }
651 }
652 
653 bool ConnectingPrivate::canCompute() const {
654  return !pending.empty();
655 }

657 void ConnectingPrivate::compute() {
658  const StatePair& top = pending.pop();
659  const InterfaceState& from = *top.first;
660  const InterfaceState& to = *top.second;
661  static_cast<Connecting*>(me_)->compute(from, to);
662 }

672 bool Connecting::compatible(const InterfaceState& from_state, const InterfaceState& to_state) const {
673  const planning_scene::PlanningSceneConstPtr& from = from_state.scene();
674  const planning_scene::PlanningSceneConstPtr& to = to_state.scene();
675 
676  if (from->getWorld()->size() != to->getWorld()->size()) {
677  ROS_DEBUG_STREAM_NAMED("Connecting", name() << ": different number of collision objects");
678  return false;
679  }
680 
681  // both scenes should have the same set of collision objects, at the same location
682  for (const auto& from_object_pair : *from->getWorld()) {
683  const collision_detection::World::ObjectPtr& from_object = from_object_pair.second;
684  const collision_detection::World::ObjectConstPtr& to_object = to->getWorld()->getObject(from_object_pair.first);
685  if (!to_object) {
686  ROS_DEBUG_STREAM_NAMED("Connecting", name() << ": object missing: " << from_object_pair.first);
687  return false;
688  }
689  if (from_object->shape_poses_.size() != to_object->shape_poses_.size()) {
690  ROS_DEBUG_STREAM_NAMED("Connecting", name() << ": different object shapes: " << from_object_pair.first);
691  return false; // shapes not matching
692  }
693 
694  for (auto from_it = from_object->shape_poses_.cbegin(), from_end = from_object->shape_poses_.cend(),
695  to_it = to_object->shape_poses_.cbegin();
696  from_it != from_end; ++from_it, ++to_it)
697  if (!(from_it->matrix() - to_it->matrix()).isZero(1e-4)) {
698  ROS_DEBUG_STREAM_NAMED("Connecting", name() << ": different object pose: " << from_object_pair.first);
699  return false; // transforms do not match
700  }
701  }
702 
703  // Also test for attached objects which have a different storage
704  std::vector<const moveit::core::AttachedBody*> from_attached;
705  std::vector<const moveit::core::AttachedBody*> to_attached;
706  from->getCurrentState().getAttachedBodies(from_attached);
707  to->getCurrentState().getAttachedBodies(to_attached);
708  if (from_attached.size() != to_attached.size()) {
709  ROS_DEBUG_STREAM_NAMED("Connecting", name() << ": different number of objects");
710  return false;
711  }
712 
713  for (const moveit::core::AttachedBody* from_object : from_attached) {
714  auto it = std::find_if(to_attached.cbegin(), to_attached.cend(),
715  [from_object](const moveit::core::AttachedBody* object) {
716  return object->getName() == from_object->getName();
717  });
718  if (it == to_attached.cend()) {
719  ROS_DEBUG_STREAM_NAMED("Connecting", name() << ": object missing: " << from_object->getName());
720  return false;
721  }
722  const moveit::core::AttachedBody* to_object = *it;
723  if (from_object->getAttachedLink() != to_object->getAttachedLink()) {
724  ROS_DEBUG_STREAM_NAMED("Connecting", name() << ": different attach links: " << from_object->getName()
725  << " attached to " << from_object->getAttachedLinkName() << " / "
726  << to_object->getAttachedLinkName());
727  return false; // links not matching
728  }
729  if (from_object->getFixedTransforms().size() != to_object->getFixedTransforms().size()) {
730  ROS_DEBUG_STREAM_NAMED("Connecting", name() << ": different object shapes: " << from_object->getName());
731  return false; // shapes not matching
732  }
733 
734  for (auto from_it = from_object->getFixedTransforms().cbegin(),
735  from_end = from_object->getFixedTransforms().cend(), to_it = to_object->getFixedTransforms().cbegin();
736  from_it != from_end; ++from_it, ++to_it)
737  if (!(from_it->matrix() - to_it->matrix()).isZero(1e-4)) {
738  ROS_DEBUG_STREAM_NAMED("Connecting", name() << ": different object pose: " << from_object->getName());
739  return false; // transforms do not match
740  }
741  }
742  return true;
743 }
744 
745 void Connecting::connect(const InterfaceState& from, const InterfaceState& to, const SolutionBasePtr& s) {
746  pimpl()->connect(from, to, s);
747 }

750  os << *stage.pimpl();
751  return os;
752 }
